  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Alpina has a fresh and contemporary style. The rooms are really cosy and combine urban and alpine styles. When you want to relax, check out the spa area and pamper yourself after a day of walking in the mountains.</p>
<h2>Enjoy scenic summer views</h2>
<p>The Hotel Alpina has a great location, not far from the centre of <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/france/chamonix" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a>. The best way to appreciate the Alpina’s location is to head to the Vista bar on the 7th floor where you’ll find an excellent drinks menu (payable locally) as well as 180° panoramic views. You can sip on a beverage whilst admiring the mighty Mont Blanc or, look down and witness the flurry of activity happening in Chamonix below.</p>
<h2>An adventure in the mountains</h2>
<p>For those after a unique experience in Chamonix, the Hotel Alpina offers the opportunity to book one unforgettable night<span> in the </span><a data-udi="umb://document/7c89165bd6bc4b71a5a7b533930f895e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c89165bd6bc4b71a5a7b533930f895e}" title="Refuge de Montenvers - Overnight Glacier Experience">Refuge du Montenvers </a>(additional charge, on request, must be booked in advance and is subject to availability). S<span>itting on the top of the Mer de Glace, high in the Chamonix Alps, it's the perfect place to watch the sun go down. This night includes a trip on the </span>Montenvers Railway which takes you to the hotel, dinner and breakfast.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
